//! # Compiler Bootstrapping
//!
//! Multi-stage self-hosting compilation infrastructure for QuantaLang:
//!
//! ## Bootstrap Stages
//!
//! | Stage | Description | Compiler Used | Output |
//! |-------|-------------|---------------|--------|
//! | 0 | Bootstrap seed | Rust | stage0/quantac |
//! | 1 | Self-hosted | stage0/quantac | stage1/quantac |
//! | 2 | Production | stage1/quantac | stage2/quantac |
//! | 3 | Verification | stage2/quantac | stage3/quantac |
//!
//! ## Verification
//!
//! The bootstrap process verifies correctness through a fundamental property:
//! **Stage 2 and Stage 3 must produce bit-identical binaries**.
//!
//! ```text
//! stage1/quantac compiles stage2/src → stage2/quantac
//! stage2/quantac compiles stage2/src → stage3/quantac
//!
//! Assertion: hash(stage2/quantac) == hash(stage3/quantac)
//! ```
//!
//! This proves the compiler is a fixed point of itself.
//!
//! ## Directory Structure
//!
//! ```text
//! build/
//! ├── stage0/
//! │   ├── bin/quantac          # Rust-compiled bootstrap
//! │   ├── lib/                 # Stage 0 stdlib
//! │   └── runtime/             # Runtime library
//! ├── stage1/
//! │   ├── bin/quantac          # Self-hosted (compiled by stage0)
//! │   ├── lib/
//! │   ├── runtime/
//! │   └── cache/               # Incremental cache
//! ├── stage2/
//! │   ├── bin/quantac          # Production compiler
//! │   ├── lib/
//! │   └── runtime/
//! └── stage3/                  # Verification only
//!     └── bin/quantac
//! ```
//!
//! ## Usage
//!
//! ```quanta
//! use bootstrap::prelude::*;
//!
//! // Configure bootstrap
//! let config = BootstrapConfig {
//!     source_dir: "src".into(),
//!     build_dir: "build".into(),
//!     target: "x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu".into(),
//!     opt_level: OptLevel::O2,
//!     verify: true,
//!     ..Default::default()
//! };
//!
//! // Run bootstrap
//! let mut bootstrap = Bootstrap::new(config);
//! let result = bootstrap.run()?;
//!
//! println!("Bootstrap complete: {:?}", result.final_compiler);
//! ```
//!
//! ## Trusted Computing Base (TCB)
//!
//! The TCB for the bootstrap consists of:
//! 1. The host Rust compiler
//! 2. The Stage 0 QuantaLang subset implementation
//! 3. System libraries (libc, etc.)
//! 4. The linker
//!
//! Minimizing Stage 0 reduces the TCB and increases trust in the final compiler.

